In .NET MAUI Shell, you can override `OnBackButtonPressed` and customize the back button. Here's the implementation:

**EditProductPage.xaml.cs**
```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior(this, new BackButtonBehavior
        {
            TextOverride = "Cancel",
            Command = new Command(async () => await TryNavigateBack())
        });
    }

    // Handles hardware/software back button (Android, etc.)
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () => await TryNavigateBack());
            return true; // cancel default navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async Task TryNavigateBack()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave) return;
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`OnBackButtonPressed`** — return `true` to cancel navigation; handles Android hardware back.
- **`Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior`** — replaces the default back arrow with a "Cancel" text button and routes taps through your logic.
- **`DisplayAlert`** — shows the confirmation dialog; navigate only if user confirms.

Set `_hasUnsavedChanges = true` whenever your form fields change (e.g., via property setters or `TextChanged` events).
